#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:1
msgid "Breakable CUDA Graph"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:3
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:5
msgid ""
"Standard CUDA graphs capture an entire forward pass as a single, opaque "
"graph. This is great for performance, but creates two problems:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:7
msgid ""
"**Debugging is hard.** When something goes wrong inside a captured graph "
"(wrong outputs, numerical mismatches, crashes), there is no way to step "
"through the operations or insert print statements because the graph replays "
"as a monolithic unit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:9
msgid ""
"**Some ops are incompatible.** Certain operations — dynamic control flow, "
"host-device synchronization, JIT compilation, or ops that change behavior "
"across iterations — cannot be captured into a CUDA graph at all. Today, the "
"only workaround is to disable CUDA graphs entirely, which sacrifices the "
"kernel launch overhead savings for the rest of the model."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:11
msgid ""
"**Breakable CUDA Graph** solves both problems by allowing graph breaks to be "
"inserted at specific points. The computation is split into multiple captured "
"graph segments with eager (non-graph) execution in between. This preserves "
"most of the CUDA graph performance benefit while allowing targeted "
"operations to run outside the graph."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:13
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:15
msgid "Debug Mode: Run Everything Eagerly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:17
msgid ""
"The simplest use case is debugging. The `--debug-cuda-graph` flag wraps the "
"entire decode forward pass in a graph break, so every operation runs eagerly "
"while still going through the full CUDA graph capture/replay code path. This "
"lets you debug CUDA graph issues without changing model code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:19
msgid ""
"python -m sglang.launch_server \\\n"
"    --model meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct \\\n"
"    --debug-cuda-graph\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:25
msgid ""
"This mode is intended for debugging only — it eliminates the performance "
"benefit of CUDA graphs since every op runs eagerly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:27
msgid "Selective Graph Breaks in Model Code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:29
msgid ""
"For production use, you can mark specific functions as \"non-graphable\" "
"using the `@eager_on_graph` decorator. During CUDA graph capture, these "
"functions run eagerly between captured graph segments. Outside of capture, "
"they behave normally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:31
msgid ""
"from sglang.srt.model_executor.breakable_cuda_graph.breakable_cuda_graph "
"import eager_on_graph\n"
"\n"
"@eager_on_graph(enable=True)\n"
"def my_dynamic_op(x):\n"
"    # This op is incompatible with CUDA graph capture\n"
"    return some_dynamic_operation(x)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:40
msgid ""
"You can also insert a bare graph break (no computation) using the "
"`break_graph()` helper:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:42
msgid ""
"from sglang.srt.model_executor.breakable_cuda_graph.breakable_cuda_graph "
"import break_graph\n"
"\n"
"def forward(self, x):\n"
"    x = self.layer1(x)\n"
"    break_graph()  # force a segment split here\n"
"    x = self.layer2(x)\n"
"    return x\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:52
msgid ""
"To enable breakable CUDA graph at the environment level (without debug "
"mode), set the environment variable:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:54
msgid ""
"export SGLANG_USE_BREAKABLE_CUDA_GRAPH=1\n"
"python -m sglang.launch_server \\\n"
"    --model meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct\n"
msgstr ""

