#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:67
msgid "How It Works"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:69
msgid "Capture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:71
msgid ""
"Breakable CUDA graph extends PyTorch's `torch.cuda.CUDAGraph` by splitting a "
"single capture into multiple segments separated by graph breaks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:73
msgid "During capture, the flow is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:75
msgid ""
"Begin capture (segment 1)\n"
"  ... graphable ops ...\n"
"  @eager_on_graph function encountered:\n"
"    1. End current capture segment\n"
"    2. Run the function eagerly (allocates output tensors)\n"
"    3. Record the function for later replay\n"
"    4. Begin new capture segment\n"
"  ... more graphable ops ...\n"
"End capture (segment N)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:87
msgid ""
"Each segment is independently instantiated as a CUDA graph executable. The "
"non-graph functions and their argument references are stored for replay."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:89
msgid "Replay"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:91
msgid "During replay:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:93
msgid ""
"For each segment i:\n"
"  1. Launch CUDA graph segment i\n"
"  2. Run the recorded non-graph function i eagerly\n"
"Launch final CUDA graph segment\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:100
msgid ""
"The non-graph functions are re-invoked with the same tensor references as "
"capture time. Since these references point to the CUDA graph's static input/"
"output buffers, they see updated values on each replay."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:102
msgid "Output Writeback"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:104
msgid ""
"When a non-graph function produces output during replay, the result must be "
"written back into the same tensor buffers that downstream graph segments "
"reference. The mechanism handles:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:106
msgid "**Plain tensors**: In-place `copy_()` into the original buffer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:107
msgid ""
"**Structured outputs** (dataclasses, objects with tensor attributes): Tensor "
"fields are copied in-place; non-tensor fields are replaced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:108
msgid ""
"**Dicts of tensors**: Tensor values are copied in-place; non-tensor values "
"are replaced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:110
msgid "Stream Fork/Join Tracking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:112
msgid ""
"Some models fork work onto secondary CUDA streams (e.g., for overlapped "
"computation). Breakable CUDA graph hooks `torch.cuda.Stream.wait_stream` to "
"track which streams are forked from the capture stream. When a graph break "
"occurs, all forked streams are automatically joined back before ending the "
"capture segment, and re-forked after beginning the next segment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:114
msgid "Compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:116
msgid ""
"**NVIDIA CUDA only.** Breakable CUDA graph is not supported on ROCm/HIP or "
"other non-CUDA platforms. On unsupported platforms, `--debug-cuda-graph` is "
"automatically disabled with a warning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:117
msgid ""
"**Requires `cuda-python`.** The `cuda.bindings` package must be installed "
"(`pip install cuda-python`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:118
msgid ""
"**Not compatible with memory saver mode.** Cannot be used together with "
"`SGLANG_MEMORY_SAVER_CUDA_GRAPH`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:120
msgid "Performance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:122
msgid ""
"When no graph breaks are inserted, breakable CUDA graph has minimal overhead "
"compared to standard CUDA graph — the capture/replay path is nearly "
"identical."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:124
msgid "Each graph break adds:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:125
msgid "One `cudaGraphLaunch` call (to replay the segment before the break)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:126
msgid "One eager Python function call"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:127
msgid ""
"One `cudaStreamBeginCapture` / `cudaStreamEndCapture` pair during capture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/breakable_cuda_graph.md:129
msgid ""
"For typical use cases with a small number of graph breaks, the overhead is "
"negligible compared to the saved kernel launch overhead from the captured "
"segments."
msgstr ""

